  "target_response": {
    "text": "HRV, heart rate variability, measures the small timing differences between consecutive heartbeats while you sleep. Bigger variability generally means your nervous system is in a rested, recover-and-adapt state; smaller variability often shows up under fatigue, stress, illness, or after hard training. The number itself only means something against your own history: your 67 ms today sits just under your 30-day average of 69.6 and close to your weekly average of 64 ms, so this is an ordinary morning for you, nothing to read into. One note on your setup: your platform calculates HRV with a different method than some devices, so comparing your number to anyone else's is meaningless. Watch your own trend line, not the raw value.",
